---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"

const LAST_UPDATED = "January 2026" // update as needed
const EMAIL = "ace@presentationace.com"
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms | Presentation Ace"
  description="Summary of standard working terms for Presentation Ace."
>
  <main class="terms">
    <div class="shell">
      <header class="terms__header">
        <p class="terms__eyebrow">Terms</p>
        <h1 class="terms__title">Working terms summary</h1>
        <p class="terms__intro">
          This page is a plain-language summary of how I typically work on
          project-based and retainer engagements. Final terms are provided in
          the proposal or agreement and may be adjusted by mutual agreement.
        </p>
        <p class="terms__updated">
          <strong>Last updated:</strong>
          {LAST_UPDATED}
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Quick summary">
        <h2 class="card__title">Quick summary</h2>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>
            <strong>Confidential by default.</strong> NDA-friendly if needed.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Project-based work:</strong> starts with a 5-hour prepaid kickoff
            block.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Retainers:</strong> billed monthly in advance, include reserved
            capacity and priority turnaround.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Rush work:</strong> may be billed at a +50% premium if needed
            in under ~3 business days or outside regular hours.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Deliverables:</strong> final PPTX plus select assets as agreed
            (not every working file by default).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Paused projects:</strong> if feedback/inputs are not received
            for 14 days, I may invoice for work completed to date.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Project-based terms">
        <h2 class="card__title">Project-based (hourly) terms</h2>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>
            <strong>Hourly billing:</strong> time is tracked and billed based on time
            spent.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Kickoff:</strong> projects start with a <strong
              >5-hour prepaid block</strong
            > to reserve time and begin work. This is credited toward the final invoice.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Invoicing:</strong> after kickoff, invoices are typically sent
            <strong>upon approval</strong> of delivered work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Paused work:</strong> if a project pauses due to missing feedback/inputs
            for <strong>14 calendar days</strong>, I may invoice for work
            completed to date. Work resumes after confirmation and payment of
            any outstanding invoices.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Turnaround:</strong> estimated turnaround depends on scope and
            capacity (I’ll provide an ETA once I review materials).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Retainer terms">
        <h2 class="card__title">Monthly retainer terms</h2>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>
            <strong>Billed monthly in advance</strong> for reserved capacity.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Priority access:</strong> retainer clients are scheduled ahead
            of project-based work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>No rush fees</strong> for updates and iterations within plan scope.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Flexible usage:</strong> hours can be used for concept, design,
            animation, and presentation consulting.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Active requests:</strong> your plan may limit how many requests
            can be active at once to keep delivery fast.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Rollover:</strong> up to <strong>10%</strong> of unused hours
            may roll over to the next month, then expire.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Overage:</strong> excess hours are billed at the standard hourly
            rate unless otherwise agreed.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Rush and turnaround">
        <h2 class="card__title">Rush work and turnaround</h2>
        <p class="text">
          I do my best to accommodate urgent needs, but rush work depends on
          capacity and existing commitments. If a request qualifies as rush, I
          will confirm before starting.
        </p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>
            <strong>Rush premium:</strong> +50% may apply for deadlines under ~3 business
            days or work outside regular hours.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Retainer priority:</strong> retainers receive first priority on
            the calendar.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Files and ownership">
        <h2 class="card__title">Files and assets</h2>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>
            <strong>Deliverables:</strong> final PPTX plus select assets as agreed.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Editable assets:</strong> when I create custom icons or flat illustrations,
            I build them as editable vectors whenever possible.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Third-party assets:</strong> any fonts, photos, icons, or other
            licensed assets remain subject to their licenses.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Confidentiality">
        <h2 class="card__title">Confidentiality</h2>
        <p class="text">
          Confidentiality is standard. I treat your decks, metrics, drafts, and
          internal materials as private. I’m happy to sign an NDA if needed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card" aria-label="Questions">
        <h2 class="card__title">Questions</h2>
        <p class="text">
          If anything here is unclear, send a quick note and I’ll clarify.
          Email:
          <a class="link" href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .terms {
      --ink: #2a2c27;
      --accent: #cf729c;
      --text: #2b2b2b;
      --muted: #6e6e6e;

      --card: #ffffff;
      --border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      --shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      --radius: 16px;

      padding: 42px 16px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .terms .shell {
      max-width: 980px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .terms__header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .terms__eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--muted);
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
    }

    .terms__title {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 2.6vw, 2.3rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ink);
    }

    .terms__intro {
      margin: 12px auto 0;
      max-width: 860px;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .terms__updated {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 18px;
      margin-top: 14px;
    }

    .card__title {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    .text {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .list {
      margin: 12px 0 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .list li {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 18px;
      margin: 10px 0;
    }

    .list li::before {
      content: "✓";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0.22em;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1;
    }

    .link {
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .link:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
